title: BBC (UK) Royal Institution Christmas Lectures 2013: (2/3)
description:
BBC (UK) Royal Institution Christmas Lectures 2013: Life Fantastic

Season 1 Episode 2 of 3

Am I a Mutant? 

Dr Alison Woollard discusses how diversity in the natural world has come from genetic mutation, and explores how species adapt and change to survive. She looks at the evolutionary theories of Charles Darwin, and the naturalist himself appears in a ghostly apparition. With guest lecturer Professor Peter Holland, an Oxford University biologist

Category Education
